Three foreign nationals were arrested after they were found one rhino horn, a lion's tooth and ivory balls. CAPE TOWN - Three suspected rhino horn and ivory peddlers have been arrested in Kuils River.The men were nabbed during routine patrols at Zevenwacht Mall on Tuesday.Following a search of a suspicious vehicle in the mall parking lot, police say they found what they believe to be one rhino horn, a lion's tooth and ivory balls.The police's Fredrick van Wyk says: While searching the vehicle, the authorities found one alleged rhino horn, 10 ivory balls and a lion tooth. The suspects are foreign nationals - one is from Zambia and the others are from the Democratic Republic of Congo. A case is under investigation by the Kuils River Stock Theft and Endangered Species Unit. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)